── DOCUMENTED BUT NOT (FULLY) IMPLEMENTED ──────────────────────────
  POST /api/users: Documented as 'Create a new user', but the
  implementation ignores the request body entirely. The user list
  is never updated; the route always returns {"status":"created"}.

── IMPLEMENTED BUT NOT DOCUMENTED ──────────────────────────────────
  405 Method-Not-Allowed catch-all: Any HTTP verb other than GET or
  POST on /api/users will reach the wildcard branch in UsersController
  and receive a 405. This behaviour is not mentioned in the README.

── KNOWN GAPS (TODOs in source) ─────────────────────────────────────
  1. POST /api/users — body is never parsed; user is never actually added to the list
  2. No authentication middleware
  3. No input validation
  4. No pagination for GET /api/users
  5. No database persistence (in-memory only)

